PUH-BrianMartell PUH_v6_Dynamo_Regimes.tex- Updated paper v6, The rebound jet dynamo operates in three distinct regimes as rotation speed ω increases: •  Kinematic regime (low ω): Magnetic field grows exponentially but remains weak. Asymmetry ΔB is negligible. •  Linear regime (intermediate ω): Dynamo reaches full strength. Magnetic asymmetry ΔB scales linearly with ω and with the geometric flaw δ. This is the regime that produces our observed matter-antimatter ratio. •  Quenching regime (high ω): Magnetic field becomes so strong it suppresses turbulence. Growth of ΔB saturates; further increase in ω yields no additional asymmetry. The transition from linear to quenching regime sets an upper limit on the possible CP asymmetry ε (and thus η_B) for any given δ.
